{"title_page": "1905 North Carolina A&M Aggies football team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox college sports team season\n| sport = football\n| year = 1905\n| team = North Carolina A&M Aggies\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| conference = Independent\n| record = 4\u20131\u20131\n| head_coach = [[George S. Whitney]]\n| hc_year = 1st\n| off_scheme = \n| def_scheme = \n| captain = \n| stadium = \n}}\n{{1905 Southern college football independents records}}\nThe '''1905 North Carolina A&M Aggies football team''' represented the [[NC State Wolfpack football|North Carolina A&M Aggies]] of [[North Carolina State University|North Carolina College of Agriculture and Mechanic Arts]] during the [[1905 college football season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gopack.com/sports/football/schedule/1902|title=1902 Football Schedule|website=NC State University Athletics}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://s3.amazonaws.com/sidearm.sites/gopack.com/documents/2016/7/25/2016MediaGuide_InsidePages.pdf |title=Media guide |publisher=s3.amazonaws.com |date= |accessdate=April 11, 2020}}</ref> in [[George S. Whitney]]'s first and only season as head coach, the Aggies compiled a record of tied 4\u20131\u20131. They tied [[1905 North Carolina Tar Heels football team|North Carolina]], the third consecutive draw in the [[North Carolina\u2013NC State football rivalry|rivalry]], and outscored their opponents 66 to 10 .\n\n==Schedule==\n{{CFB schedule\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 28\n| w/l = w\n| opponent = [[1905 VMI Keydets football team|VMI]]\n| site_stadium = \n| site_cityst = [[Raleigh, North Carolina|Raleigh, NC]]\n| score = 5\u20130\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 7\n| w/l = l\n| away = y\n| opponent = [[1905 Virginia Cavaliers football team| Virginia]]\n| site_stadium = Madison Hall Field\n| site_cityst = [[Charlottesville, Virginia|Charlottesville, VA]]\n| score = 0\u201310\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 26\n| w/l = w\n| opponent = [[1905 South Carolina Gamecocks football team|South Carolina]]\n| site_stadium = \n| site_cityst = Raleigh, NC\n| gamename = [[NC State\u2013South Carolina football rivalry|rivalry]]\n| score = 29\u20130\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = November 12\n| w/l = t\n| opponent = [[1905 North Carolina Tar Heels football team|North Carolina]]\n| site_stadium = \n| site_cityst = Raleigh, NC\n| gamename = [[North Carolina\u2013NC State football rivalry|rivalry]]\n| score = 0\u20130\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = November 18\n| w/l = w\n| opponent = [[1905 Washington and Lee Generals football team|Washington and Lee]]\n| site_stadium = \n| site_cityst = Raleigh, NC\n| score = 22\u20130\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = November 30\n| w/l = w\n| opponent = {{cfb link|year=1905|team=Davidson|title=Davidson}}\n| site_stadium = \n| site_cityst = [[Winston-Salem, North Carolina|Winston-Salem, NC]]\n| score = 10\u20130\n}}\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{NC State Wolfpack football navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1905 North Carolina AandM Aggies football team}}\n[[Category:1905 college football season|North Carolina AandM]]\n[[Category:NC State Wolfpack football seasons]]\n[[Category:1905 in sports in North Carolina|North Carolina AandM Football]]\n\n{{Collegefootball-1900s-season-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox college sports team season\n| sport = football\n| year = 1905\n| team = North Carolina A&M Aggies\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| conference = Independent\n| record = 4\u20131\u20131\n| head_coach = [[George S. Whitney]]\n| hc_year = 1st\n| off_scheme = \n| def_scheme = \n| captain = \n| stadium = \n}}\n{{1905 Southern college football independents records}}\nThe '''1905 North Carolina A&M Aggies football team''' represented the [[NC State Wolfpack football|North Carolina A&M Aggies]] of [[North Carolina State University|North Carolina College of Agriculture and Mechanic Arts]] during the [[1905 college football season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gopack.com/sports/football/schedule/1902|title=1902 Football Schedule|website=NC State University Athletics}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://s3.amazonaws.com/sidearm.sites/gopack.com/documents/2016/7/25/2016MediaGuide_InsidePages.pdf |title=Media guide |publisher=s3.amazonaws.com |date= |accessdate=Aprul 11, 2020}}</ref> in [[George S. Whitney]]'s first and only season as head coach, the Aggies compiled a record of tied 4\u20131\u20131. They tied [[1905 North Carolina Tar Heels football team|North Carolina]], the third consecutive draw in the [[North Carolina\u2013NC State football rivalry|rivalry]], and outscored their opponents 66 to 10 .\n\n==Schedule==\n{{CFB schedule\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 28\n| w/l = w\n| opponent = [[1905 VMI Keydets football team|VMI]]\n| site_stadium = \n| site_cityst = [[Raleigh, North Carolina|Raleigh, NC]]\n| score = 5\u20130\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 7\n| w/l = l\n| away = y\n| opponent = [[1905 Virginia Cavaliers football team| Virginia]]\n| site_stadium = Madison Hall Field\n| site_cityst = [[Charlottesville, Virginia|Charlottesville, VA]]\n| score = 0\u201310\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 26\n| w/l = w\n| opponent = [[1905 South Carolina Gamecocks football team|South Carolina]]\n| site_stadium = \n| site_cityst = Raleigh, NC\n| gamename = [[NC State\u2013South Carolina football rivalry|rivalry]]\n| score = 29\u20130\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = November 12\n| w/l = t\n| opponent = [[1905 North Carolina Tar Heels football team|North Carolina]]\n| site_stadium = \n| site_cityst = Raleigh, NC\n| gamename = [[North Carolina\u2013NC State football rivalry|rivalry]]\n| score = 0\u20130\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = November 18\n| w/l = w\n| opponent = [[1905 Washington and Lee Generals football team|Washington and Lee]]\n| site_stadium = \n| site_cityst = Raleigh, NC\n| s